From: "trieu2.huynh" <trieu2.huynh@lge.corp-partner.google.com>
Date: Wed, 8 Jul 2026 13:52:45 +0900
Subject: [PATCH 1/2] binder: test: fix RT inheritance failure in binder
 latency test

The real-time (RT) priority inheritance currently report fails as
"inheritance": "FAIL" during 'schd-dbg' execution.

By default, BBinder utilizes lazy allocation for its mExtras pointer.
Without an explicit configuration, isInheritRt() returns false, causing
the FLAT_BINDER_FLAG_INHERIT_RT flag to be omitted in [1].
Consequently, the binder kernel driver forcibly drops the server
thread's priority from RT to SCHED_NORMAL during the FIFO thread
transaction [2].

Fix this by explicitly calling `setInheritRt(true)` in the
BinderWorkerService constructor to properly propagate the RT flag.

[1] https://cs.android.com/android/platform/superproject/+/android-latest-release:frameworks/native/libs/binder/Parcel.cpp;l=326
[2] https://cs.android.com/android/kernel/superproject/+/common-android-mainline:common/drivers/android/binder.c;l=826

Bug: 532013252
Test: m schd-dbg
Test: Manual - Run schd-dbg and verify that "inheritance" outputs "PASS"

Change-Id: I2788a93a9a757c94b478d65a2247ebeae6321f60
Signed-off-by: trieu2.huynh <trieu2.huynh@lge.corp-partner.google.com>
---
 libs/binder/tests/schd-dbg.cpp | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

diff --git a/libs/binder/tests/schd-dbg.cpp b/libs/binder/tests/schd-dbg.cpp
index 0035e4e..22b4690 100644
--- a/libs/binder/tests/schd-dbg.cpp
+++ b/libs/binder/tests/schd-dbg.cpp
@@ -99,6 +99,7 @@ void thread_dump(const char* prefix) {
 class BinderWorkerService : public BBinder {
  public:
   BinderWorkerService() {
+    setInheritRt(true);
   }
   ~BinderWorkerService() {
   }
